 Exercise 2: OSINT (Open Source Intelligence) Research

 Objective
Gather publicly available information about a target.

 Methodology
1. Google Search: Used advanced search operators
2. Social Media: Checked LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook
3. Public Records: Searched WHOIS, business directories
4. Image Analysis: Reverse image search

Tools
- Google Dorking
- Maltego (free version)
- Social-searcher.com
- HaveIBeenPwned

 Results
Found:
- Employee names and positions
- Email format patterns
- Physical address
- Previous data breaches

 Security Implications
- Information leakage can enable spear phishing
- Public data helps attackers craft convincing pretexts

 Protection Measures
- Limit personal information online
- Use privacy settings on social media
- Regularly audit digital footprint
